  "textPreview": "Free June 9 event: How to win brand visibility when AI decides what gets seen →\nSolutions\nTools\nResources\nPricing\nEN\nSign in\nRequest a demo\nStart free trial\nGemini Visibility Tracker\n\nImprove your brand’s visibility in Google Gemini. See where and how your brand is mentioned, benchmark competition, and monitor shifts over time with our top-notch Gemini visibility tracking software\n\nStart free trial\nRequest a demo\n\nNo credit card required\n\nTrusted by 40,000+ agencies\n\nGemini Visibility Tracker\n\nGet Google Gemini brand visibility insights\n\nReview Gemini’s answers to your target keywords\n\nTrack Gemini brand mentions and website links\n\nSee how Gemini ranks your brand in responses\n\nMonitor and analyze competitor visibility\n\nGet historical data on your Gemini performance\n\nStart free trial\nGet the full view of your brand across Gemini and other AI engines to protect your reputation, make marketing decisions, and guide narratives\nTry now\nGemini brand presence tracking that covers every angle\n\nMeasure every aspect of your Gemini brand visibility with precision\n\nTrack brand mentions in Gemini’s answers\n\nCheck how Gemini mentions your brand. Analyze context, phrasing, and messages to understand how your brand is presented to users.\n\nAssess your brand’s Gemini visibility\n\nTrack the frequency of your brand mentions and site links in Gemini responses. See the changes over time and grow your presence.\n\nCompare visibility with key competitors\n\nBenchmark your brand’s visibility against top competitors. Identify who is mentioned, how often and where, and how you compare.\n\nSpot opportunities to boost Gemini rankings\n\nAnalyze gaps in your brand’s Gemini AI visibility and find new ways to get mentioned more often. Earn higher placements across AI answers.\n\nIdentify the sources Gemini trusts\n\nCheck which domains and URLs Gemini cites in its responses to your target prompts. Understand whether it favors media, blogs, or forums.\n\nMonitor Gemini visibility across markets and languages\n\nTrac",
